126       public String[] getYearSemesters(int year) {
127           // Lose the first two numbers of the year
128           int semester = year % 100;
129           boolean returnBoolean = false;
130           /*
131            * Contains the year in YYYY form, the previous, current and next
132            * semester in that order.
133            */
134           String[] semesters = new String[4];
135           semesters[0] = "" + year;
136           switch (semester) {
137           /*
138            * If the given year is 2001-2008, (year % 100) will give a single
139            * number below 9. Therefore, the previous, current and next semester
140            * all need a leading 0 added.
141            */
142           case 0:
143               semesters[1] = "WS" + "99" + "00";
144               semesters[2] = "SS" + "00";
145               semesters[3] = "WS" + "00" + "01";
146               break;
147           case 1:
148           case 2:
149           case 3:
150           case 4:
151           case 5:
152           case 6:
153           case 7:
154           case 8:
155               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
156               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
157               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + "0" + (semester + 1);
158               break;
159           /*
160            * If the given year is 2009, the previous and current semester will
161            * both be a single number and therefore need a leading 0 added. The
162            * next semester will be 10 and thus needs no adjustments.
163            */
164           case 9:
165               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
166               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
167               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + (semester + 1);
168               break;
169           /*
170            * If the given year is 2010, the current and next semesters will be 10
171            * and 11 and therefore don't need a leading 0. The previous semester
172            * will be 9 though.
173            */
174           case 10:
175               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + semester;
176               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
177               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
178               break;
179           case 99:
180               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
181               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
182               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + "00";
183               break;
184           /*
185            * In all other relevant cases (11 and higher), the semesters can be
186            * used the way (year % 100) returns them.
187            */
188           default:
189               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
190               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
191               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
192               break;
193           }
194           return semesters;

289        *
290        * @return The vector of years as ints.
291        */
292       public Vector getYears() {
293           Vector semesters = getSemesters();
294           if (semesters.size() > 0) {
295               /*
296                * Only get the years, if there are any valid courses with a
297                * semester.
298                */
299               Vector years = new Vector();
300               /*
301                * Check for every semester out of the semester vector, if the year
302                * of that semester is already noted and add it if it's not.
303                */
304               for (Object semester : semesters) {
305                   char[] semesterChar = ((String) semester).toCharArray();
306                   int year = 0;
307                   if (Character.isDigit(semesterChar[0])) {
308                       // The semester is in the form YYYY.
309                       for (int i = 0; i < semesterChar.length; i++) {
310                           year = year
311                                   + Character.getNumericValue(semesterChar[i])
312                                   * (int) Math.pow(10, 3 - i);
313                       }
314                   } else {
315                       // The semester is in the form SSYY or WSYYYY.
316                       int i = 0;
317                       while (!Character.isDigit(semesterChar[i])) {
318                           i++;
319                       }
320                       int power = 0;
321                       switch (semesterChar.length - i) {
322                       case 2:
323                           // The semester is in the form SSYY
324                           year = 2000;
325                           power = 10;
326                           for (int j = i; j < semesterChar.length; j++) {
327                               year = year
328                                       + Character
329                                           .getNumericValue(semesterChar[j])
330                                       * power;
331                               if (power == 10) {
332                                   power = 1;
333                               } else {
334                                   power = 10;
335                               }
336                           }
337                           break;
338                       case 4:
339                           /*
340                            * The semester is in the form WSYYYY. Both semester
341                            * years must be checked
342                            */
343                           for (int l = 0; l < 3; l = l + 2) {
344                               year = 2000;
345                               power = 10;
346                               for (int j = i + l; j < semesterChar.length
347                                       - (2 - l); j++) {
348                                   year = year
349                                           + Character
350                                               .getNumericValue(semesterChar[j])
351                                           * power;
352                                   if (power == 10) {
353                                       power = 1;
354                                   } else {
355                                       power = 10;
356                                   }
357                               }
358                               if (!years.contains(year)) {
359                                   years.add(year);
360                               }
361                           }
362                           break;
363                       }
364                   }
365                   if (!years.contains(year)) {
366                       years.add(year);
367                   }
368               }
369               Vector sortedYears = new Vector();
370               sortedYears.add(years.get(0));
371               for (int i = 1; i < years.size(); i++) {
372                   boolean addedYear = false;
373                   for (int j = 0; j < sortedYears.size(); j++) {
374                       if ((Integer) years.get(i) <= (Integer) sortedYears.get(j)) {
375                           sortedYears.add(j, years.get(i));
376                           addedYear = true;
377                           break;
378                       }
379                   }
380                   if (!addedYear) {
381                       sortedYears.add(years.get(i));
382                   }
383               }
384               return sortedYears;
385           } else {
386               /*
387                * There are no valid courses. Return empty vector.
388                */
389               Vector years = new Vector();
390               return years;
391           }

379       /**
380        * Creates the balance reports of the year by calling the functions to
381        * create all semesters of the year.
382        *
383        * @param year
384        *            The year to be added.
385        */
386       private void createYear(int year) {
387           // Lose the first two numbers of the year
388           int semester = year % 100;
389           /*
390            * Contains the year in YYYY form, the previous, current and next
391            * semester in that order.
392            */
393           String[] semesters = new String[4];
394           semesters[0] = Integer.toString(year);
395           switch (semester) {
396           /*
397            * If the given year is 2001-2008, (year % 100) will give a single
398            * number below 9. Therefore, the previous, current and next semester
399            * all need a leading 0 added.
400            */
401           case 0:
402               semesters[1] = "WS" + "99" + "00";
403               semesters[2] = "SS" + "00";
404               semesters[3] = "WS" + "00" + "01";
405               break;
406           case 1:
407           case 2:
408           case 3:
409           case 4:
410           case 5:
411           case 6:
412           case 7:
413           case 8:
414               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
415               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
416               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + "0" + (semester + 1);
417               break;
418           /*
419            * If the given year is 2009, the previous and current semester will
420            * both be a single number and therefore need a leading 0 added. The
421            * next semester will be 10 and thus needs no adjustments.
422            */
423           case 9:
424               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + "0" + semester;
425               semesters[2] = "SS0" + semester;
426               semesters[3] = "WS0" + semester + (semester + 1);
427               break;
428           /*
429            * If the given year is 2010, the current and next semesters will be 10
430            * and 11 and therefore don't need a leading 0. The previous semester
431            * will be 9 though.
432            */
433           case 10:
434               semesters[1] = "WS0" + (semester - 1) + semester;
435               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
436               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
437               break;
438           case 99:
439               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
440               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
441               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + "00";
442               break;
443           /*
444            * In all other relevant cases (11 and higher), the semesters can be
445            * used the way (year % 100) returns them.
446            */
447           default:
448               semesters[1] = "WS" + (semester - 1) + semester;
449               semesters[2] = "SS" + semester;
450               semesters[3] = "WS" + semester + (semester + 1);
451               break;
452           }
453           // Check if the semester has a course and add it if it does.
454           for (String currentSemester : semesters) {
455               if (courseExists(currentSemester)) {
456                   createSemester(currentSemester);
457               }
458           }
459       }

461       /**
462        * Checks if the given semester contains any courses.
463        *
464        * @param semester
465        *            The semester to check
466        * @return true if the semester contains one or more courses.
467        */
468       private boolean courseExists(String semester) {
469           List<ICourse> courses = null;
470           try {
471               courses = (new Course()).getAll();
472           } catch (Exception e) {
473               e.printStackTrace();
474           }
475           // Check for every course, if it belongs to the given semester.
476           for (ICourse course : courses) {
477               if (course.getSemester().equals(semester)) {
478                   return true;
479               }
480           }
481           return false;
482       }

44       public Translation(String language) {
45           /* Create path if necessary */
46           filePath = Runtime.getInstance().getConfigPath() + "lang/";
47  
48           File languagePath = new File(filePath);
49           if ((!languagePath.exists() || !languagePath.isDirectory())
50                   && !languagePath.mkdirs()) {
51               System.err.println("Couldn't create directory for translations.");
52           }
53  
54           /* Load the language file */
55           InputStream inputStream = null;
56  
57           /* Check first in .jar */
58           String jarfile = Runtime.getInstance().getJarLocation();
59           if (jarfile.endsWith(".jar")) {
60               inputStream = getClass().getClassLoader().
61                       getResourceAsStream("de/aidger/lang/de.properties");
62           }
63  
64           /* After that check in filesystem */
65           if (inputStream == null) {
66               try {
67                   File inputFile = new File(filePath + language + ".properties");
68                   inputStream = new FileInputStream(inputFile);
69               } catch (Exception e) {
70                   Logger.error("Loading the translation from the filesystem failed. Only english will be available");
71               }
72           }
73  
74           /* Finally load the resource */
75           if (inputStream != null) {
76               try {
77                   bundle = new PropertyResourceBundle(inputStream);
78                   inputStream.close();
79               } catch (IOException ex) {
80               }
81           }
82       }
83  
84       /**
85        * Returns the translation of the specified string from the bundle.
86        *
87        * @param id
88        *            The string to translate.
89        * @return The translated string or return the id.
90        */
91       public static String _(String id) {
92           try {
93               return bundle.getString(id);
94           } catch (Exception e) {
95               /*
96                * If the string is not translated in the bundle, or the bundle
97                * cannot be found, just return the original string.
98                */
99               return id;
100           }
101       }
102  
103       /**
104        * Get a list of all languages installed on the system. The format is 0 =>
105        * short, 1 => long language name.
106        *
107        * @return The list of all installed languages
108        */
109       public List<Pair<String, String>> getLanguages() {
110           List<Pair<String, String>> list = new Vector<Pair<String, String>>();
111  
112           /* Add English as standard language */
113           list.add(new Pair<String, String>("en", new Locale("en")
114               .getDisplayLanguage()));
115  
116           /* Search all translations in the jar file */
117           try {
118               JarFile jf = new JarFile(Runtime.getInstance().getJarLocation());
119               Enumeration ress = jf.entries();
120  
121               while (ress.hasMoreElements()) {
122                   JarEntry je = (JarEntry) ress.nextElement();
123  
124                   int idx = je.getName().indexOf(".properties");
125                   if (idx > -1) {
126                       String lang = je.getName().substring(idx - 2, idx);
127                       list.add(new Pair<String, String>(lang, new Locale(lang)
128                               .getDisplayLanguage()));
129                   }
130               }
131           } catch (IOException ex) {
132           }
133  
134           /* Search all files in the lang directory and add them */
135           File[] files = (new File(filePath)).listFiles();
136           if (files != null) {
137               for (File file : files) {
138                   String filename = file.getName();
139                   int idx = filename.indexOf(".properties");
140                   if (idx > -1) {
141                       String lang = filename.substring(0, idx);
142                       list.add(new Pair<String, String>(lang, new Locale(lang)
143                           .getDisplayLanguage()));
144                   }
145               }
146           }
147  
148           return list;
149       }
150   }

11   public abstract class Validator {

19        * The members of the model to check.
20        */
21       protected String[] members;
22  
23       /**
24        * The error message.
25        */
26       protected String message;
27  
28       /**
29        * Initialize the PresenceValidator class.
30        */
31       public Validator() {
32           this.model = null;
33           this.members = new String[0];
34           this.message = _("Default error");

36

38        * Initialize the PresenceValidator class.
39        *
40        * @param model
41        *            The model to validate
42        * @param members
43        *            The members of the model to validate
44        */
45       public Validator(AbstractModel model, String[] members) {
46           this.model = model;
47           this.members = members;
48           this.message = _("Default error");
49       }
50  
51       /**
52        * Validate the input.
53        *
54        * @return True if it validates
55        */
56       public boolean validate() {
57           boolean ret = true;
58           for (String member : members) {
59               Object value = getValueOf(member);
60               if (!validateVar(value)) {
61                   ret = false;
62                   if (model != null) {
63                       model.addError(member, message);
64                   }
65               }
66           }
67           return ret;
68       }

71        * Validate the variable.
72        *
73        * @param o
74        *            The variable to validate
75        * @return True if the input validates, false otherwise
76        */
77       abstract public boolean validateVar(Object o);
78  
79       /**
80        * Set the error message.
81        *
82        * @param msg
83        *            The new error message
84        */
85       public void setMessage(String msg) {
86           message = msg;
87       }
88  
89       /**
90        * Get the error message.
91        *
92        * @return The error message.
93        */
94       public String getMessage() {
95           return message;
96       }
97  
98       /**
99        * Get the value of the given member variable.
100        *
101        * @param name
102        *            The name of the member variable
103        * @return The value of the member variable or null
104        */
105       protected Object getValueOf(String name) {
106           String functionname = "get" + name.substring(0, 1).toUpperCase()
107                   + name.substring(1);
108           try {
109               java.lang.reflect.Method m = model.getClass().getDeclaredMethod(
110                       functionname, new Class<?>[0]);
111               return m.invoke(model, new Object[0]);
112           } catch (Exception ex) {
113               try {
114                   return model.getClass().getField(name).get(model);
115               } catch (Exception e) {
116                   return null;
117               }
118           }
119       }
120  
121   }

45           List<IActivity> activities = null;
46           try {
47               activities = new Activity().getAll();
48           } catch (AdoHiveException e1) {
49               // TODO Auto-generated catch block
50               e1.printStackTrace();
51           }
52           Calendar currentDate = Calendar.getInstance();
53           // Display all activities if numberOfDays == -1.
54           if (numberOfDays != -1) {
55               currentDate.add(Calendar.DATE, (-numberOfDays));
56           } else {
57               currentDate.setTimeInMillis(-3600000);
58           }
59           for (IActivity activity : activities) {
60               /**
61                * If the date of the activity is after, or equal to the
62                * currentDate, it lies within the wanted time frame.
63                */
64               if (currentDate.getTime().before(activity.getDate())
65                       || activity.getDate().equals(currentDate.getTime())) {
66                   try {
67                       addedActivity = new Object[8];
68                       addedActivity[0] = (new Assistant().getById(activity
69                           .getAssistantId())).getFirstName()
70                               + " "
71                               + (new Assistant().getById(activity
72                                   .getAssistantId())).getLastName();
73                       addedActivity[1] = (new Course().getById(activity
74                           .getCourseId())).getDescription();
75                       addedActivity[2] = activity.getType();
76                       addedActivity[3] = activity.getDate();
77                       addedActivity[4] = activity.getContent();
78                       addedActivity[5] = activity.getSender();
79                       addedActivity[6] = activity.getProcessor();
80                       addedActivity[7] = activity.getRemark();
81                       addedActivities.add(addedActivity);
82                   } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
83                       // TODO Auto-generated catch block
84                       e.printStackTrace();
85                   }
86               }
87           }
88           return addedActivities;
89       }

22        */
23       private final Vector balanceReportGroupCreators = new Vector<Vector>();
24  
25       /**
26        * The balance helper used to filter the courses in this creator.
27        */
28       private BalanceHelper balanceHelper = null;
29  
30       /**
31        * Initializes this BalanceReportSemesterCreator and adds the groups of the
32        * given semester.
33        *
34        * @param semester
35        *            The semester of which the groups shall be added.
36        * @throws AdoHiveException
37        */
38       public BalanceReportSemesterCreator(String semester, BalanceFilter filters)
39               throws AdoHiveException {
40           balanceHelper = new BalanceHelper();
41           addGroups(semester, filters);
42       }
43  
44       /**
45        * Adds the groups to the semester viewer.
46        *
47        * @param semester
48        *            The semester of which to add the groups.
49        */
50       private void addGroups(String semester, BalanceFilter filters) {
51           List<ICourse> courses = null;
52           try {
53               courses = (new Course()).getAll();
54           } catch (AdoHiveException e) {
55               // TODO Auto-generated catch block
56               e.printStackTrace();
57           }
58           List<ICourse> filteredCourses = balanceHelper.filterCourses(courses,
59               filters);
60           for (ICourse course : filteredCourses) {
61               if (course.getSemester().equals(semester)) {
62                   if (balanceReportGroupCreators.isEmpty()) {
63                       /*
64                        * If there are no groups in the semester yet, add a new
65                        * one.
66                        */
67                       createGroup(course);
68                   } else {
69                       boolean foundGroup = false;
70                       for (int i = 0; i <= balanceReportGroupCreators.size() - 1; i++) {
71                           if (((Vector) balanceReportGroupCreators.get(i)).get(1)
72                               .equals(course.getGroup())) {
73                               /*
74                                * If the course group already exists in this
75                                * semester, add another row to it with this course.
76                                */
77                               ((BalanceReportGroupCreator) ((Vector) balanceReportGroupCreators
78                                   .get(i)).get(0)).addCourse(course);
79                               foundGroup = true;
80                               break;
81                           }
82                       }
83                       if (!foundGroup) {
84                           /*
85                            * If the course group wasn't in the semester yet, add a
86                            * new group.
87                            */
88                           createGroup(course);
89                       }
90                   }
91               }
92           }
93       }
94  
95       /**
96        * Creates a new group and adds it to the balanceReportGroupCreators vector.
97        *
98        * @param course
99        *            The first course, which the group contains.
100        */
101       private void createGroup(ICourse course) {
102           BalanceReportGroupCreator balanceReportGroupCreator = new BalanceReportGroupCreator(
103               course);
104           balanceReportGroupCreators.add(new Vector<Object>());
105           int i = balanceReportGroupCreators.size() - 1;
106           /*
107            * Add the group creator of this course's group as the first entry of
108            * the vector.
109            */
110           ((Vector) balanceReportGroupCreators.get(i))
111               .add(balanceReportGroupCreator);
112           /*
113            * Add the name of the group as the second entry of the vector.
114            */
115           ((Vector) balanceReportGroupCreators.get(i)).add(course.getGroup());
116           ((BalanceReportGroupCreator) ((Vector) balanceReportGroupCreators
117               .get(i)).get(0)).addCourse(course);
118       }

51        * Provides access to an instance of this class.

62  
63       /**
64        * Resolves the OS of the user and the file path to the aidGer settings.
65        */
66       public void initialize() {
67           /* Get the path to the users home or config directory */
68           String home = "";
69           String os = System.getProperty("os.name").toLowerCase();
70           if (os.indexOf("linux") > -1 || os.indexOf("mac") > -1) {
71               /*
72                * Try using the XDG_CONFIG_DIR variable first. Provides the
73                * standard directory according to the desktop guidelines or a user
74                * set equivalent
75                */
76               String confdir = System.getenv("XDG_CONFIG_HOME");
77               if (confdir == null || confdir.isEmpty()) {
78                   /*
79                    * Otherwise just use the homedir and the hidden config
80                    * directory
81                    */
82                   confdir = System.getProperty("user.home", ".");
83                   confdir += "/.config/";
84               }
85               home = confdir;
86           } else if (os.indexOf("windows") > -1) {
87               /*
88                * Try using the APPDATA variable first. Should return the
89                * ApplicationData folder but may fail on older Windows versions.
90                */
91               String confdir = System.getenv("APPDATA");
92               if (confdir == null || confdir.isEmpty()) {
93                   /* Otherwise just use the homedir */
94                   confdir = System.getProperty("user.home", ".");
95               }
96               home = confdir;
97           } else {
98               home = System.getProperty("user.home", ".");
99           }
100  
101           configPath = home + "/aidGer/";
102           File file = new File(configPath);
103  
104           if ((!file.exists() || !file.isDirectory()) && !file.mkdirs()) {
105               UI.displayError(MessageFormat.format(
106                       "Could not create directory \"{0}\".\n" +
107                       "Please make sure that you have enough rights to create this directory.",
108                       new Object[] { file.getPath() }));
109               System.exit(-1);
110           }
111  
112           configuration = new Configuration();
113  
114           translation = new Translation(configuration.get("language"));
115  
116           /* Check if an instance of aidGer is already running */
117           if (!Boolean.valueOf(getOption("debug")) && !checkLock()) {
118               UI.displayError(_("Only one instance of aidGer can be run at a time."));
119               System.exit(-1);
120           }
121       }

142       /**
143        * Returns the location and name of the .jar file.
144        *
145        * @return The location
146        */
147       public String getJarLocation() {
148           String location = getClass().getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().
149                   getLocation().toString();
150           int idx = location.indexOf(":");
151  
152           /* Windows uses file:/C:/folder whereas Unix uses file:/folder */
153           if (idx != location.lastIndexOf(":")) {
154               location = location.substring(idx + 2);
155           } else {

161        * Save the current model to the database.
162        *
163        * @return True if validation succeeds
164        * @throws AdoHiveException
165        */
166       @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
167       public boolean save() throws AdoHiveException {
168           if (!doValidate()) {
169               return false;
170           } else if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
171               Logger
172                   .debug(_("The model was not saved because the error list is not empty."));
173               return false;
174           }
175  
176           /* Add or update model */
177           IAdoHiveManager mgr = getManager();
178           if (isNew) {
179               Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Adding model: {0}"),
180                   new Object[] { toString() }));
181  
182               mgr.add(this);
183               setNew(false);
184           } else if (updatePKs) {
185               Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Updating PKs for model: {0}"),
186                   new Object[] { toString() }));
187  
188               mgr.remove(pkModel);
189               mgr.add(this);
190               pkModel = (AbstractModel<T>) clone();
191           } else {
192               Logger.info(MessageFormat.format(_("Updating model: {0}"),
193                   new Object[] { toString() }));
194  
195               mgr.update(this);
196           }
197  
198           setChanged();
199           notifyObservers(true);
200  
201           return true;
202       }

213               return false;
214           }

216           /* Check if there is a custom validation function */
217           try {
218               java.lang.reflect.Method m = getClass().getDeclaredMethod(
219                   "validateOnRemove");
220               if (!(Boolean) m.invoke(this, new Object[0])) {
221                   return false;
222               }
223           } catch (Exception ex) {
224           }

227               new Object[] { toString() }));

229           getManager().remove(this);

231           notifyObservers(false);

411       @Override
412       public String toString() {
413           String ret = getClass().getSimpleName() + " [" + "ID: " + getId()
414                   + ", ";
415           try {
416               for (java.lang.reflect.Method m : getClass().getDeclaredMethods()) {
417                   if (m.getName().startsWith("get")
418                           && m.getParameterTypes().length == 0) {
419                       ret += m.getName().substring(3) + ": ";
420                       ret += m.invoke(this, new Object[0]) + ", ";
421                   }
422               }
423               if (ret.endsWith(", ")) {
424                   ret = ret.substring(0, ret.length() - 2);
425               }
426           } catch (Exception ex) {
427               System.err.println(ex.getMessage());
428           }
429           return ret + "]";
430       }

433        * Extract the name of the class and return the correct manager.
434        *
435        * @return The name of the model class
436        */
437       @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
438       protected IAdoHiveManager getManager() {
439           String classname = getClass().getSimpleName();
440           if (!managers.containsKey(classname) || managers.get(classname) == null) {
441               /* Try to get the correct manager from the AdoHiveController */
442               try {
443                   java.lang.reflect.Method m = AdoHiveController.class
444                       .getMethod("get" + classname + "Manager");
445                   managers.put(classname, (IAdoHiveManager) m.invoke(
446                       AdoHiveController.getInstance(), new Object[0]));
447               } catch (Exception ex) {
448                   Logger.error(MessageFormat.format(
449                       _("Could not get manager for class \"{0}\". Error: {1}"),
450                       new Object[] { classname, ex.getMessage() }));
451               }
452           }
453  
454           return managers.get(classname);
455       }

466               if (!v.validate()) {

472           try {
473               java.lang.reflect.Method m = getClass().getDeclaredMethod(
474                   "validate");
475               if (!(Boolean) m.invoke(this, new Object[0])) {
476                   ret = false;
477               }
478           } catch (Exception ex) {
479           }

481           return ret;
